        truth="New families find her through the studio Facebook page, a Wix website contact form that forwards to her Gmail, and word-of-mouth; she replies by text to book a trial lesson, and if it goes well she pencils the student into a recurring weekly slot on the paper wall planner she keeps by the piano. The weekly schedule for herself and her three contract teachers lives in a Google Sheet she rebuilds from scratch every August. The CORE work is the teaching itself: she personally teaches about 35 back-to-back 30- and 60-minute private lessons a week — roughly 25 hours of face-to-face instruction, Monday through Thursday from 2:30 to 8pm plus Saturday mornings — choosing and adapting each student's repertoire by ear out of the Faber and RCM books and hand-writing that week's practice assignments into each kid's paper practice notebook. Recitals twice a year she books at a local church and organizes over email and Facebook. Monthly tuition is billed by hand: she tallies attended and makeup lessons from sticky notes and the planner into the Google Sheet, texts or emails each family their amount, and collects by Venmo, Zelle, check, or cash, chasing late payers by text. At month-end she hand-calculates each contract teacher's 60% split from the same sheet and pays them by Zelle.",
