        truth="New families find Little Sprouts by word of mouth and the center's Facebook page; the owner-director books tours by text, keeps the waitlist in a spiral notebook, and hands enrolling parents a printed paper packet plus the state immunization and emergency-contact forms. The CORE work is her own hands-on early-learning care and instruction — feeding, diapering, running circle time, and leading lesson activities — which she personally delivers 6-8 hours a day working the floor of the infant or toddler room to hold state-mandated child-to-staff ratios whenever a teacher calls out (most days), all while directing a building of roughly 40 children across four classrooms from 6:30am to 6pm. Teachers document every diaper, bottle, nap, and mood by hand on carbon-copy daily sheets that go home at pickup, and sign-in/out is a paper clipboard by the door. She tracks tuition in an Excel spreadsheet, parents pay by check, Zelle, or Venmo, and she chases late payments by text. For subsidy families she re-keys each month's attendance into the state childcare-assistance portal, and re-enrollment packets go back out to every family each August.",
